        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death , park the vehicle on a flat level
                        surface, set the parking brake, chock the wheels and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, allow the engine to cool adequately before performing this Service
                        Procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tie strap securing the old bracket to the lower radiator pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut and washer holding the bracket to the oil pan.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new bracket to the oil pan. Tighten to 15 to 19 Lbf-ft (20 to 26 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new clamp around the lower radiator hose and fasten to the new bracket with
                    a 3/8 inch bolt, washer, and nut. Tighten to 34 to 38 Lbf-ft (46 to 52 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
